On Windows:

a. Open the Start menu and search for "Environment Variables."

b. Click on "Edit the system environment variables."

c. In the System Properties window, click the "Environment Variables" button.

d. Under the "System variables" section, scroll down and find the "Path" variable. Select it and click the "Edit" button.

e. In the Edit Environment Variable window, add the path to the directory containing the new Python executable at the beginning of the list. For example, if you installed Python in C:\Python39, add C:\Python39 to the list of paths.

f. Click "OK" to save the changes.
